      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:66:12",
      "text": [
        " مَنْ أَنْصَفَ النَّاسَ مِنْ نَفْسِهِ رُضِيَ بِهِ حَكَماً لِغَيْرِهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Mahboub, from one of his companions, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The one who is fair with the people from himself, would be pleased with judging for others’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "12. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn Mahbub from certain individuals of his people from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “Whoever yields to justice for people against his own soul is accepted to judge others’ cases.” "
        ]
      }
